Solution:
The area of the triangle is $\frac{1}{2}bh$, where $b$ is the length of the base and $h$ is the height.  Here, the base is $2x$ and the height is $x$, so the area of the triangle is $\frac{1}{2}(2x)(x)=x^2$.  We set this equal to 64 and solve for $x$: \begin{align*}
x^2&=64\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=\boxed{8}.
\end{align*}

